==English==

''usage note'': Savor is the American spelling and Savour is chiefly British


===Noun===
'''savor'''
# the specific [[taste]] or [[smell]] of something
# a [[distinctive]] [[sensation]]
===Verb===
'''to savor''' (''transitive'' or ''intransitive'')
# to possess a particular taste or smell, or a distinctive quality
# to [[appreciate]], [[enjoy]] or [[relish]] something
===Alternative spellings===
*[[savour]] (''Chiefly British'')